S3 Class

Source: R/s3.R
S3.Rd

An R6 interface to Metaflow's S3 client. This class provides methods for interacting with S3, including connecting, listing, and retrieving objects. It uses the S3Client class internally for AWS authentication and client management.

Method new()

Create a new S3 object.

Usage

S3$new(
  tmproot = ".",
  bucket = NULL,
  prefix = NULL,
  run = NULL,
  s3root = NULL,
  verbose = FALSE,
  mf = .globals[["mf"]]
)

Arguments

tmproot

Character string specifying the temporary directory root.

bucket

Optional character string specifying the S3 bucket.

prefix

Optional character string specifying the S3 prefix.

run

Optional Metaflow Run object or FlowSpec.

s3root

Optional character string specifying the S3 root path.

verbose

Logical, if TRUE, print detailed error messages.

mf

Metaflow object, defaults to .globals["mf"].

Method get()

Get a single object from S3

Usage

S3$get(key = NULL, return_missing = FALSE, return_info = TRUE)

Arguments

key

Character string or S3GetObject representing the S3 key

return_missing

Logical, if TRUE, return missing keys as S3Objects with exists = FALSE

return_info

Logical, if TRUE, fetch content-type and user metadata

Returns

An S3Object

Method get_many()

Get multiple objects from S3

Usage

S3$get_many(keys, return_missing = FALSE, return_info = TRUE)

Arguments

keys

Character vector or list of S3GetObjects representing the S3 keys

return_missing

Logical, if TRUE, return missing keys as S3Objects with exists = FALSE

return_info

Logical, if TRUE, fetch content-type and user metadata

Returns

A list of S3Objects

Method list_paths()

List the next level of paths in S3.

Usage

S3$list_paths(keys = NULL)

Arguments

keys

Optional character vector of keys to list. If NULL, lists from the S3 root.

Returns

A list of S3Object representations.

Method list_recursive()

List all objects recursively under the given prefixes.

Usage

S3$list_recursive(keys = NULL)

Arguments

keys

Optional character vector of keys to list. If NULL, lists from the S3 root.

Returns

A list of S3Object representations.

Method get_recursive()

Get objects from S3 recursively

Usage

S3$get_recursive(keys, return_info = FALSE)

Arguments

keys

Character vector of keys or prefixes to download recursively

return_info

Logical, if TRUE, fetch content-type and user metadata

Returns

A list of S3Objects

Method get_all()

S3$get_all(return_info = FALSE)

return_info

Method put()

Put a single object to S3

Usage

S3$put(key, obj, overwrite = TRUE, content_type = NULL, metadata = NULL)

Arguments

key

Character string or S3PutObject representing the S3 key

obj

Object to store in S3

overwrite

Logical, if TRUE, overwrite existing object

content_type

Optional MIME type for the object

metadata

Optional list of metadata to store with the object

Returns

Character string of the URL of the stored object

Method put_many()

Put multiple objects to S3

Usage

S3$put_many(key_objs, overwrite = TRUE)

Arguments

key_objs

List of key-object pairs or S3PutObjects

overwrite

Logical, if TRUE, overwrite existing objects

Returns

List of character vectors, each containing key and URL of stored object

Method put_files()

Put multiple files to S3

Usage

S3$put_files(key_paths, overwrite = TRUE)

Arguments

key_paths

List of key-path pairs or S3PutObjects

overwrite

Logical, if TRUE, overwrite existing objects

Returns

List of character vectors, each containing key and URL of stored object

Method clone()

The objects of this class are cloneable with this method.

Usage

S3$clone(deep = FALSE)

Arguments

deep

Whether to make a deep clone.
